This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it proposes a new method to improve the retrieval effectiveness of tag-based event retrieval systems. It also involves machine learning-based query expansion approach, which is a common technique used in information retrieval. 

The paper also deals with media sharing applications and image retrieval, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

The use of statistical exploratory analysis of spatial point patterns to extract geo-spatial features indicates that it could also belong to the Spatial Informatics (cs.SI) sub-category. 

The paper involves the use of features and similarity measures, which are common in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of databases to store and retrieve information, which suggests that it could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
